- add branch predictor and btb
- make execution unit ooo and add retire unit 
- vector extension
- ...?

Planned core features:
- RV32IMAFDV
- speculative
- in-order frontend
    - out-of-order execution unit:
    - if first stage of the execution unit is free, and instruction is not dependent on an incomplete load in the second stage of the execution unit, then instruction can execute out-of-order
- single issue
- RV32I isa

- 2 stage frontend
    - 1. instruction fetch, 2. decode + register fetch in parallel
    - simple branch predictor and BTB
    - small RAS 
    - small L0-I and L0-D
    - simple next-line L0 prefetcher

- 1-2 stage execution unit:
    - 1. alu ops, adress generation, branch resolution, ... (EX1)
    - 2. if memory op, instruction continues here until completion (EX2)
- 1 stage retire unit (RET)
    - ensure instructions are committed in-order
    - writes back to registers

